Package com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller

Class GoodController

java.lang.Object
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller.BaseController<Good,GoodRepository,GoodDTO,GoodService>
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller.GoodController
@Controller @RequestMapping(path="/api/v1/good") public class GoodController extends BaseController<Good,GoodRepository,GoodDTO,GoodService>
Controller responsible for handling HTTP requests related to the Good entity. It extends the generic BaseController to provide CRUD operations for Good entities and adds a custom method for searching goods by name. This controller uses the GoodService to interact with the database and perform operations on Good entities.

  • Method Details

    • getEntities

      @GetMapping(value="/find", produces="application/json") @ResponseBody public List<Good> getEntities(@RequestParam String name)
      Retrieves a list of Good entities whose names contain the specified substring. This method allows for searching the database for goods based on partial name matches, facilitating user search operations in the application.
      Parameters:
      name - The substring to search for within Good entity names.
      Returns:
      A list of Good entities that contain the specified substring in their names.
